README
info:
Email messages from the ship (every 30 minutes)
are sent to a gmail account.

The gmail account forwards to mqttinbox.com

The mqttinbox submits the messages (as raw emails)
to mqtt.marine.ie, so they show up in a kafka queue.

This process in node-red parses the underway data
from the email message, and stores to cassandra.

ERDDAP uses cassandra as the backend for the underway
dataset.
